Interface Tuples.Tuple

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Tuples.Five<A,​B,​C,​D,​E>, Tuples.Four<A,​B,​C,​D>, Tuples.Six<A,​B,​C,​D,​E,​F>, Tuples.Three<A,​B,​C>, Tuples.Two<A,​B>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Tuples.FiveImpl, Tuples.FourImpl, Tuples.SixImpl, Tuples.ThreeImpl, Tuples.TwoImpl
    Enclosing class:
    Tuples
    public static interface Tuples.Tuple
    This common interface for tuples is convenient for writing utilities or code that needs to handle all tuples uniformly. This type of usage is rare, since you lose the generic typing and access to the individual values in the tuple.

      • values

        java.util.stream.Stream<java.lang.Object> values()
        A stream of the values contained in the Tuple. The purpose of tuples is to store arbitrary pairs of values (or more), and the types of the values are likely to be different. Therefore, this treats them all as Objects. Usage of this method should be rare, as a Collection would usually be a better fit.
        Returns:
        a Stream containing all values in the tuple.
